        <h2>WELCOME TO YUMTHANG VALLEY</h2>
        <p>Yumthang Valley in North Sikkim is a stunning natural wonder known as the "Valley of Flowers," where vivid rhododendrons, primulas, and other alpine blooms transform the landscape in spring. Set at an altitude of 3,564 meters (11,693 feet), the valley is surrounded by towering Himalayan peaks and lush pine forests, creating a breathtaking panorama. The Yumthang River flows through this picturesque valley, adding to its serene beauty with its crystal-clear waters. In winter, the valley transforms into a snowy wonderland, attracting visitors with its quiet, otherworldly charm. Yumthang is also near the renowned Shingba Rhododendron Sanctuary, making it a paradise for nature lovers and trekkers who seek peace and scenic beauty amidst the untouched wilderness of North Sikkim.






        </p>

